<h3>States in the South-South</h3>
<dl>
  <dt> <b> Rivers State </b> </dt>
  <dd>This state was created in 1967, by the Yakubu Gowon military Government. It originally comprised of present-day Rivers State and Bayelsa State, but the Ijaw Rivers (as Bayelsa was known) was granted autonmy in 1996. 
